WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:11.000
The Oxford Bookworms, Starters, Police TV, by Tim Vickery, read by Vincenzo Niccoli.

00:11.000 --> 00:29.000
Published and copyright, Oxford University Press 2000.

00:29.000 --> 00:34.000
1. The Jogger.

00:34.000 --> 00:39.000
Dan and Sue are police officers in London.

00:39.000 --> 00:45.000
It is a Tuesday morning and Dan is angry.

00:45.000 --> 00:49.000
What's the matter, Dan? Sue asks.

00:49.000 --> 00:53.000
Look at this, Dan says.

00:53.000 --> 00:58.000
Every day someone steals money from people near the shops.

00:58.000 --> 01:01.000
We must stop this.

01:01.000 --> 01:04.000
Yes, of course, Sue says.

01:04.000 --> 01:07.000
But who is it?

01:07.000 --> 01:10.000
There is a Jogger, Dan says.

01:10.000 --> 01:14.000
Every day he runs near the shops.

01:14.000 --> 01:18.000
Sometimes he runs into people.

01:18.000 --> 01:21.000
Perhaps he steals the money.

01:21.000 --> 01:24.000
OK, Sue says.

01:24.000 --> 01:26.000
Let's go to the shops.

01:26.000 --> 01:31.000
Perhaps we can see this Jogger.

01:31.000 --> 01:35.000
They sit upstairs in a window over the shops.

01:35.000 --> 01:38.000
Dan has a radio.

01:38.000 --> 01:42.000
They watch the people in the street.

01:42.000 --> 01:45.000
Look, Sue says.

01:45.000 --> 01:48.000
There's the Jogger.

01:48.000 --> 01:54.000
The young man runs into an old woman and she falls down.

01:54.000 --> 01:58.000
The Jogger puts his hand on the old woman's arm.

01:58.000 --> 02:01.000
I'm sorry, he says.

02:01.000 --> 02:03.000
Can I help you?

02:03.000 --> 02:06.000
Here's your bag.

02:06.000 --> 02:09.000
Then a young woman shouts at him.

02:09.000 --> 02:12.000
Don't run here, she says.

02:12.000 --> 02:16.000
It's dangerous. Go away.

02:16.000 --> 02:19.000
The young man runs away.

02:19.000 --> 02:22.000
Dan talks in his radio.

02:22.000 --> 02:25.000
Quick, stop him.

02:25.000 --> 02:28.000
He's running up North Street.

02:28.000 --> 02:33.000
A police car stops the young man in North Street.

02:33.000 --> 02:36.000
Are you OK now?

02:36.000 --> 02:39.000
Sue asks the old woman.

02:39.000 --> 02:42.000
Yes, thank you.

02:42.000 --> 02:45.000
Where is that nice young woman?

02:45.000 --> 02:48.000
I can't see her now.

02:48.000 --> 02:53.000
Have you got all your money, Sue asks?

02:53.000 --> 02:57.000
The old woman looks in her bag.

02:57.000 --> 03:00.000
No, I haven't.

03:00.000 --> 03:03.000
My money's in my purse.

03:03.000 --> 03:06.000
But my purse isn't here.

03:06.000 --> 03:10.000
OK, Sue, Dan says.

03:10.000 --> 03:13.000
Let's talk to the Jogger.

03:15.000 --> 03:19.000
Who are you, Sue asks the young man.

03:19.000 --> 03:22.000
My name's Peter Jones.

03:22.000 --> 03:26.000
Why? Who are you?

03:26.000 --> 03:29.000
We're police officers.

03:29.000 --> 03:33.000
Why do you go running past the shops every day?

03:33.000 --> 03:36.000
Why not? I like running.

03:36.000 --> 03:39.000
OK, Dan says.

03:39.000 --> 03:42.000
Let's look for the money.

03:42.000 --> 03:45.000
What money? Peter Jones asks.

03:45.000 --> 03:47.000
What are you talking about?

03:47.000 --> 03:52.000
I never take money with me when I run.

03:52.000 --> 03:58.000
Dan looks for the money, but he cannot find any.

03:58.000 --> 04:02.000
Can I go now? Peter Jones asks.

04:02.000 --> 04:05.000
OK, Dan says angrily.

04:05.000 --> 04:08.000
But don't come back.

04:08.000 --> 04:11.000
Why not? Peter asks angrily.

04:11.000 --> 04:13.000
I live here.

04:13.000 --> 04:16.000
And I'm not doing anything wrong.

04:16.000 --> 04:19.000
He runs away.

04:19.000 --> 04:23.000
What do we do now, Sue asks?

04:23.000 --> 04:28.000
Where is the old woman's money and her purse?

04:28.000 --> 04:31.000
I don't know, says Dan.

04:31.000 --> 04:35.000
Somebody has it, but who?

04:42.000 --> 04:49.000
Chapter 2. TV.

04:49.000 --> 04:54.000
Dan and Sue go back to the shops.

04:54.000 --> 05:00.000
I don't understand. Dan says.

05:00.000 --> 05:06.000
The Jogger hasn't got the money, so we must look for someone different.

05:07.000 --> 05:10.000
Look, Sue says.

05:10.000 --> 05:14.000
There's a TV camera over that shop door.

05:14.000 --> 05:18.000
Perhaps that can help us.

05:18.000 --> 05:22.000
They go into the shop and watch the video.

05:22.000 --> 05:25.000
Look, Sue says.

05:25.000 --> 05:27.000
There's the old woman.

05:27.000 --> 05:32.000
She's getting money from the bank and putting it into her purse.

05:33.000 --> 05:37.000
Now she's putting the purse into the bag.

05:37.000 --> 05:41.000
Stop the video there, says Dan.

05:41.000 --> 05:45.000
Now, look carefully.

05:45.000 --> 05:49.000
Is anybody watching her?

05:49.000 --> 05:53.000
There are a lot of people in the street, Sue says.

05:53.000 --> 05:55.000
I'm not sure.

05:55.000 --> 05:59.000
Is it that man with the long hair?

05:59.000 --> 06:02.000
Perhaps, says Dan.

06:02.000 --> 06:04.000
Let's go on.

06:04.000 --> 06:07.000
What happens next?

06:07.000 --> 06:10.000
They watch the video.

06:10.000 --> 06:14.000
The Jogger runs into the old lady.

06:14.000 --> 06:17.000
He stops and helps her.

06:17.000 --> 06:21.000
She shouts at him and he runs away.

06:21.000 --> 06:26.000
Then a lot of people come and help the old lady.

06:26.000 --> 06:29.000
Look, Sue says.

06:29.000 --> 06:33.000
The long-haired man has her arm.

06:33.000 --> 06:38.000
Yes, but that woman has her bag, Dan says.

06:38.000 --> 06:40.000
What's she doing with it?

06:40.000 --> 06:44.000
Oh, I can't see.

06:44.000 --> 06:48.000
There's a man in front of her.

06:48.000 --> 06:53.000
Listen, I have an idea, Dan says.

06:53.000 --> 06:58.000
You go to the bank tomorrow and take some money out.

06:58.000 --> 07:02.000
Why is that a good idea, Sue asks?

07:02.000 --> 07:06.000
Because we can watch you, Dan answers.

07:06.000 --> 07:12.000
Get a lot of money from the bank and let everybody in the street see it.

07:12.000 --> 07:17.000
Take a radio, too, so you can talk to me.

07:17.000 --> 07:19.000
Okay, Sue says.

07:19.000 --> 07:22.000
We can do that tomorrow morning then.

07:33.000 --> 07:35.000
Chapter three.

07:35.000 --> 07:39.000
Help me. Quick.

07:39.000 --> 07:43.000
Next day, Sue goes to the bank.

07:43.000 --> 07:47.000
Dan is watching with another policeman, Jim.

07:47.000 --> 07:51.000
They have radios.

07:51.000 --> 07:55.000
I'm getting the money now, Sue says.

07:55.000 --> 07:57.000
That's good, Sue.

07:57.000 --> 08:00.000
Dan says on his radio.

08:00.000 --> 08:04.000
Now let everybody see it.

08:04.000 --> 08:07.000
Sue drops the money near her feet.

08:07.000 --> 08:12.000
People in the street look at her.

08:12.000 --> 08:17.000
Look, there's the man with the long hair, Jim says.

08:17.000 --> 08:20.000
He's picking up the money.

08:20.000 --> 08:22.000
Shall I arrest him?

08:22.000 --> 08:26.000
No, wait, Dan says.

08:26.000 --> 08:29.000
Watch.

08:29.000 --> 08:34.000
The man picks up the money and gives it to Sue.

08:34.000 --> 08:36.000
Here you are, he says.

08:36.000 --> 08:38.000
That's a lot of money.

08:38.000 --> 08:41.000
Be careful.

08:41.000 --> 08:44.000
Thanks, Sue says.

08:44.000 --> 08:46.000
That's okay.

08:46.000 --> 08:50.000
The man smiles and walks away.

08:50.000 --> 08:52.000
Have you got all the money, Sue?

08:52.000 --> 08:55.000
Dan asks by radio.

08:55.000 --> 08:59.000
Yes, it's all here, Sue says.

08:59.000 --> 09:03.000
What can I do now?

09:03.000 --> 09:08.000
Buy some things in the shops and then walk slowly down the street.

09:08.000 --> 09:13.000
Dan says, we're watching you.

09:13.000 --> 09:18.000
Sue buys some apples, milk and bread.

09:18.000 --> 09:22.000
Then she walks slowly down the street.

09:22.000 --> 09:27.000
Dan and Jim watch her go.

09:27.000 --> 09:31.000
Is anybody following me, Sue asks?

09:31.000 --> 09:35.000
No, Dan says.

09:35.000 --> 09:40.000
There's a woman with a baby, that's all.

09:40.000 --> 09:44.000
Don't follow me, Sue says into the radio.

09:44.000 --> 09:47.000
Nobody must see you.

09:47.000 --> 09:51.000
I'm turning right into Smith Street.

09:51.000 --> 09:56.000
Now I'm turning left into Peg Lane.

09:56.000 --> 10:00.000
The woman with the baby is following me.

10:00.000 --> 10:05.000
I'm turning right into Dale Avenue.

10:05.000 --> 10:07.000
Are there lots of people about?

10:07.000 --> 10:09.000
Dan asks.

10:09.000 --> 10:12.000
No, it's very quiet.

10:12.000 --> 10:16.000
Nothing is happening.

10:16.000 --> 10:19.000
Dan and Jim wait.

10:19.000 --> 10:22.000
Then Sue shouts, be careful.

10:22.000 --> 10:27.000
Oh, help me. Quick. Help.

10:27.000 --> 10:33.000
The jogger, Peter Jones, runs into Sue and she falls over.

10:33.000 --> 10:39.000
There are apples, milk and bread everywhere.

10:39.000 --> 10:44.000
I'm sorry, says the man. Let me help you.

10:44.000 --> 10:47.000
The woman takes Sue's arm.

10:47.000 --> 10:51.000
Are you okay? She asks.

10:51.000 --> 10:56.000
Go away. She shouts at the man.

10:56.000 --> 11:00.000
But he sees the radio in Sue's pocket.

11:00.000 --> 11:03.000
What's this? He asks.

11:03.000 --> 11:05.000
A police radio?

11:05.000 --> 11:08.000
Give me the money. Quick.

11:08.000 --> 11:13.000
He takes the money and runs.

11:13.000 --> 11:18.000
The woman wants to run after him, but Sue holds her.

11:18.000 --> 11:21.000
Stop, she says.

11:21.000 --> 11:23.000
I'm a police officer.

11:23.000 --> 11:26.000
He must stay here.

11:26.000 --> 11:29.000
But why? The woman asks.

11:29.000 --> 11:36.000
I want to help you. That man has your money. I haven't got it.

11:36.000 --> 11:40.000
Is he your friend? Sue asks.

11:40.000 --> 11:42.000
Where does he live?

11:42.000 --> 11:46.000
I don't know. The woman says.

11:46.000 --> 11:49.000
I don't know him.

11:49.000 --> 11:52.000
Who are you? Sue asks.

11:52.000 --> 11:55.000
Where do you live?

11:55.000 --> 11:57.000
Linda.

11:57.000 --> 12:03.000
Linda Wilkes. I live at 14 Old Street.

12:15.000 --> 12:20.000
Chapter 4, Man with a Knife.

12:20.000 --> 12:23.000
Dan runs up to Sue.

12:23.000 --> 12:27.000
Are you okay? He asks.

12:27.000 --> 12:30.000
Yes, I'm okay. She says.

12:30.000 --> 12:34.000
Go on, Dan. Run.

12:34.000 --> 12:38.000
Sue calls a police car on her radio.

12:38.000 --> 12:42.000
Dan runs after Peter Jones.

12:42.000 --> 12:46.000
Jim, he's turning left into Doc Lane.

12:46.000 --> 12:51.000
He shouts. Can you see him?

12:51.000 --> 12:56.000
I can see him, but he's running very fast, Jim says.

12:56.000 --> 13:00.000
The jogger sees Jim and gets into a boat.

13:00.000 --> 13:05.000
Jim runs to the river and gets into the boat too.

13:05.000 --> 13:08.000
Stop, Jim says.

13:08.000 --> 13:12.000
I'm a police officer. Oh, no.

13:12.000 --> 13:18.000
The jogger, Peter Jones, hits Jim and he falls into the water.

13:18.000 --> 13:22.000
The boat goes across the river.

13:22.000 --> 13:26.000
Dan helps Jim out of the water.

13:26.000 --> 13:30.000
He's going into a cafe, Dan says.

13:30.000 --> 13:34.000
Come on. Let's run to that bridge.

13:34.000 --> 13:39.000
They go across the bridge and run to the cafe.

13:39.000 --> 13:44.000
Jim goes behind the cafe and Dan goes in.

13:44.000 --> 13:48.000
Is he in there? Jim asks on his radio.

13:48.000 --> 13:51.000
Yes, Dan answers.

13:51.000 --> 13:54.000
Jim, he's coming out.

13:54.000 --> 13:57.000
Stop, says Jim.

13:57.000 --> 14:00.000
I'm a police officer.

14:00.000 --> 14:04.000
But Peter has a knife in his hand.

14:04.000 --> 14:07.000
Jim holds out his hand.

14:07.000 --> 14:11.000
Give me the knife, Peter.

14:11.000 --> 14:14.000
Stay back, Peter says.

14:14.000 --> 14:17.000
I can kill you with this.

14:17.000 --> 14:21.000
Jim can see Dan in the door behind Peter.

14:21.000 --> 14:27.000
Dan walks out of the door very slowly and quietly.

14:27.000 --> 14:32.000
Come on, Peter, says Jim. Give me the knife.

14:32.000 --> 14:36.000
Dan takes Peter's arms from behind

14:36.000 --> 14:39.000
and Jim takes the knife from his hand.

14:39.000 --> 14:44.000
Dan finds the money in Peter's trousers.

14:54.000 --> 15:00.000
Chapter 5, at the police station.

15:00.000 --> 15:04.000
I want to go home now, says Linda.

15:04.000 --> 15:08.000
My baby is hungry and tired.

15:08.000 --> 15:11.000
Do you know Peter Jones, Sue asks?

15:11.000 --> 15:15.000
Do you and Peter steal money from people?

15:15.000 --> 15:21.000
No, I don't know him and I never steal money.

15:21.000 --> 15:25.000
Do you know this woman, Peter? Dan asks.

15:25.000 --> 15:29.000
No, says Peter.

15:29.000 --> 15:33.000
I don't know her. Who is she?

15:34.000 --> 15:39.000
Dan and Sue go back to their office.

15:39.000 --> 15:44.000
Does Linda work with Peter? Dan asks Sue.

15:44.000 --> 15:48.000
Yes, she does, says Sue.

15:48.000 --> 15:54.000
Watch this video. Look, there she is.

15:54.000 --> 16:00.000
She's watching me get the money and now she's talking to someone on her phone.

16:00.000 --> 16:06.000
But who is she talking to? She's talking to Peter, of course.

16:06.000 --> 16:13.000
Now she's following me and talking to him again. She's talking about me.

16:13.000 --> 16:18.000
Dan and Sue speak to Linda again.

16:18.000 --> 16:24.000
Can I see your phone, please, Miss Wilkes? Sue asks.

16:24.000 --> 16:28.000
My phone? Why do you want to see that?

16:28.000 --> 16:32.000
Well, it remembers a lot of numbers.

16:32.000 --> 16:39.000
Sue presses one on Linda's phone. Peter's phone begins to ring.

16:39.000 --> 16:42.000
Sue laughs.

16:42.000 --> 16:48.000
Let me ask you again, Miss Wilkes. Do you know Peter Jones?

16:48.000 --> 16:55.000
Well, yes, okay. I know him. But I don't steal money.

16:56.000 --> 17:03.000
Sue and Dan take Linda home. They go into her house.

17:03.000 --> 17:08.000
There's 200 pounds under your bed, Linda, Dan says.

17:08.000 --> 17:13.000
And look, this is the old lady's purse.

17:13.000 --> 17:18.000
This is a nice photo of you and the baby, Sue says.

17:18.000 --> 17:23.000
But who is the man? Is he the baby's father?

17:23.000 --> 17:31.000
Okay. It's Peter, says Linda. And yes, I do steal the money.

17:31.000 --> 17:34.000
I'm sorry, okay?

17:34.000 --> 17:41.000
No, Linda. It's not okay, Sue says. It's not okay at all.

